<CENTER><H2>HIGH TIMES FAQ FILE</H2></CENTER>

<FONT FACE="verdana, arial, geneva, sans-serif" SIZE="4"><B>GENERAL INFORMATION REGARDING HIGH TIMES MAGAZINE</B></FONT><P>

1. <B>What does "420" mean?</B><BR>
Basically it means "time to smoke pot" or "pot smoking," as 4:20 is usually done at 4:20 PM or AM. But there's more to it than that. In fact, there are several different versions of the origin of "420."<P>

"420" was allegedly a police code for "marijuana smoking in progress" in certain California counties. (Another variation of the myth, from the book <I>Storming Heaven-LSD and the American Dream</I> and written by Jay Stevens, says that the first dose of LSD was taken by Albert Hofmann at 4:20 PM.) At any rate, some smokers began to use "420" to refer to their own "marijuana smoking in progress." It wasn't long before 4:20 became "tea-time" for many people who began to enjoy using "let's 420" instead of "let's smoke some pot."<P>

After awhile, April 20 (4/20) began to take on some significance and became known as "The Stoner New Year." Even more bizarre, some people began to develop a "420 fetish." They formed "420 Clubs" instead of Bong Teams, smoking only at 4:20 AM and PM, waiting all day before they lit up a joint (or bong or whatever), and would wake up at 4:20 AM to indulge.<P>

There has even been a 4:20 backlash. People have formed "8:40 Clubs," where they smoke twice as much as people do at 4:20. They have smoked out at 2:10, to get an early jump. They smoke every hour on the hour at twenty minutes past, since it's always 4:20 somewhere. Meanwhile entire industries have grown up around the "420" banner. There is a 420 Records, a "420 Productions," and of course, a <A HREF="http://www.420.com/">www.420.com</A> Web site.<P>

