3. <B>I am looking for some information on urine tests/I need to know about how to pass a urine test/Is there any known reliable way to pass a urinalysis if you only smoke pot/etc.?</B><BR>
Please check the <A HREF="../Reference/Testing/index.tpl">Drug Tests</A> section on the HIGH TIMES home page. This contains some current information on urine tests. If you have any more questions call the HIGH TIMES Hotline (1-900-988-8463), or the NORML 900-Line (1-900-97-NORML).<P>

Due to the many differences in metAboutlism, different types of urine test, blood tests, and hair tests, and legal complications we have decided not to post the information on how to pass a drug test on the Web site for now. Also, we believe the best way to pass a drug test is to REFUSE TO TAKE ONE.<P>

Drug tests are unconstitutional, unreliable, and the worst invasion of personal privacy that anyone could ever think of. The only way to stop drug testing is to sue the companies that try to force you to take one, refuse to buy products from companies that drug test employees (which is difficult, because so many companies drug test employees), and refuse to take them.<P>

Remember, t<B>hese drug tests are NOT 100% reliable</B> so anyone who never took illegal drugs can flunk, and anyone who might have ingested illegal drugs can pass. Worst of all, many companies are not even interested in illegal drug use. They are inspecting people's urine for genetic predisposition toward certain diseases or medical conditions. When you allow a company to drug test you are giving them much more personal information that they should ever know.<P>

We do not wish to encourage people to use masks or tricks to pass drug tests, we want you to help us stop them altogether. For that reason we are reformatting the section to encourage people from not taking these tests. If you are intent on taking a job that requires you to take a pre-employment drug test, then we strongly suggest you stop smoking for a few months, clean out your system, and do your job interviews. If you take a job that requires periodical drug testing, you are really faced with a choice: stop smoking, or risk losing your job.<P> 

4. <B>Can you tell me how to get some seeds/Can you tell me where to get some good buds/Does HIGH TIMES sell marijuana and marijuana paraphernalia through the Internet?</B>
HIGH TIMES provides articles, facts and debates  about recreational and medicinal drugs to adults for informational purposes only. We do not encourage the recreational use of drugs. There are other sites, or perhaps even some advertisers on this site or others on the Internet, that will be only too glad to help you with these questions. For instance, if you go to the Yahoo search engine and type in "cannabis seeds" a number of international seed banks will be listed.<P>

We've received a number of questions concerning the Dutch seed companies--especially the Sensi Seed Bank. They do not mail seeds to the United States--they only do business in Holland, where it is legal to grow cannabis/hemp/marijuana for seed production.<P>

<B>NOTE:</B> Throughout HIGH TIMES' long history, the vast majority of marijuana consumers have refused to join NORML or contribute any money to the cause of marijuana legalization because they are afraid their "name will end up on a list." Yet many of these same people will pay someone they barely know for seeds or pot--and their names end up on a list. This despite the fact that no one has ever been arrested for contributing to activist organizations. (In fact, many people who belong to activist groups enjoy a large support system if they are arrested on marijuana charges).<P>

There have been dozens of sting operations run by DEA agents and undercover narcotics officers where they sell marijuana seeds from small advertisements in newspapers, leaflet campaigns, cultivation stores, and other apparently legitimate operations. Lately, web sites offering Dutch seeds for sale have been showing up, enticing customers to buy pot seeds. 
These operations could very well be DEA fronts, or could end up busted by the Feds and then coerced into entrapping people who do business with them. IT IS ILLEGAL TO BUY SEEDS THROUGH THE MAIL. DON'T DO IT. 
Any legitimate seed company will not sell or mail seeds to America. If they do, they are not to be trusted, and you could end up busted.<P>


5. <B>What is the Cannabis Cup?</B><BR>
The Cannabis Cup was founded by Steven Hager in 1988 in order to establish an international standard for cannabis seeds. He modeled it after the harvest festivals held in California in the 1970s, where growers would bring their finest buds to a public gathering and tasting and a winner would be judged.
Over the years, the Cannabis Cup has grown from a small meeting of a handful of select celebrities and HIGH TIMES editors to a convention of hundreds of people from all over the world. For the last few years it has been held in Amsterdam during the traditional, American, Thanksgiving holiday weekend. 
As a result, many public weed contests bill themselves as "The Cannabis Cup," but accept no substitutions. If it's not the Official HIGH TIMES Cannabis Cup, it's not the real thing.<P>

6. <B>What is skunk?</B><BR>
Skunk was originally Skunk #1, the first winner of the HIGH TIMES Cannabis Cup in 1988 and one of the first superstar varieties of indoor marijuana. Soon street dealers were calling their product "skunk," and the term soon became a code word for high-quality buds.<P>

7. <B>What is sinsemilla?</B><BR>
Sinsemilla is marijuana that grown under conditions where the female plants have been separated from the males. This causes the female plants to ooze more resin in search of male pollination so that the plant can produce seeds.<P> 

Many connoisseurs prefer the seedless sinsemilla to seedy buds, but there are those purists who feel that sex-starved female plants cause an unnatural stress in the plant, and prefer the lower-grade, but more natural, sexed marijuana.<P> 

