Remember that whenever you order grow supplies from any store, Web site, or service. that you should NEVER mention or refer to cannabis, marijuana seeds, or any kind of illegal activity. I<P>

15. <B>I/my friend/my relative just got busted. Where can I get legal help?</B><BR>
NORML (norml.org) features a national legal referral service. If they can't help you, call the local BAR association. Don't pick the first guy that comes around--set up an appointment, meet with them, and make sure you feel comfortable that they can handle your defense.<P>

16. <B>I heard HIGH TIMES said the best pot is grown in my state/I heard my college is the Number One Party College according to HIGH TIMES magazine/etc.</B><BR>
HIGH TIMES magazine has never declared that any one state has the best pot in the country. And HIGH TIMES has never run a poll of the country's best party towns or colleges.<P>

Occasionally a statement like this will be made in the Pot 40, but we don't have a master database to be able to look up every vote ever published (yet).<P>

17. <B>How can I get involved in the movement to legalize marijuana?</B>
First, join NORML. Although this is not the most effective thing that can be done, increasing their membership is the most important thing that needs to be done.<P>

Second, become informed. Read as much as you can about the current laws, about any medical risks and benefits of cannabis, about the history of drug prohibition, about the politicians who are passing our laws and about how these laws can be changed.<P>

Write to your local, state and federal representatives and express your point of view. Encourage them to end the Drug War.<P>

Write letters to newspapers and magazines expressing your point of view.<P>

