20. <B>I am visiting the Caribbean/Amsterdam/Wherever soon and want to know where I can buy marijuana while I am there. How can I smuggle some back with me? And I can't find any connections where I live. Can you help me?</B><BR>
First, do not carry anything with you when you travel to any foreign country. Their jails are often harsh places to live. Second, HIGH TIMES does not publish, or even know of, places where people can buys drugs. Third, even if we did know, the police would find out and bust anyone who went there.<P>

Also, it's never wise to try to smuggle anything from a foreign country home with you. The risks (going to jail for life) outweigh the benefits (saving a few dollars). Also, drug smugglers are experts in their field. Amateurs should not try this at home.<P>

Finally, HIGH TIMES is not about to give people information about how/where to buy illegal drugs. Besides, if you don't know how to make friends who share common interests with you by now, it's too late for us to help you. 
